<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm44799696">
<term>budget constraint</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm64008240">all possible consumption combinations of goods that someone can afford, given the prices of goods, when all income is spent; the boundary of the opportunity set</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm73717184">
<term>law of diminishing marginal utility</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm72372000">as we consume more of a good or service, the utility we get from additional units of the good or service tend to become smaller than what we received from earlier units</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm27324704">
<term>marginal analysis</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm79845280">examination of decisions on the margin, meaning a little more or a little less from the status quo</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm75719264">
<term>opportunity cost</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm71117248">measures cost by what is given up in exchange; opportunity cost measures the value of the forgone alternative</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp68834864">
<term>opportunity set</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm95170176">all possible combinations of consumption that someone can afford given the prices of goods and the individual’s income</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp18026640">
<term>sunk costs</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm46264448">costs that are made in the past and cannot be recovered</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm103067632">
<term>utility</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm89027792">satisfaction, usefulness, or value one obtains from consuming goods and services</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>

